author: @WDDYPP
text:
I think those people who are just gonna take everything so literally and hate on people just doing their job & creating music for the rest of us, gotta stop listening to at least 90% of the music out there. Almost every title and every song content could be a trauma?! If the song has gunshots= trigger. Dynamite/explosion = trigger. Sex-related = trigger. At this point, even if the song talks about eating meat, are the vegans gonna bash it?! Geez. 
Also the live incident has nothing to do with the actual music? 20 boys talking over each other on live, it was already chaotic. When I first watched it, I only heard chenle saying it was covid siren to wear mask. They probably thought it was that. And when the staff said earthquake, you canâ€™t even really hear the word Jeju until Kun repeated it. But take note that Kunâ€™s voice was caught through mic which is clear to us when we watch the video but when they are sitting there, honestly you canâ€™t confirm every single one of the guys heard it or even looked at the prompter (if there was) of the staff writing earthquake or Jeju earthquake. The coincidence of them literally just promoting their song before the siren was just unfortunate. They probably thought the staff wanted more content on their song earthquake. ğŸŒ anyway, no reason to spread hate. Seems like they realised what was going on after and wrote apologies just in case they hurt anyoneâ€™s feelings. But some people decided to take their apology and twist it all around, acting like if you apologised means you definitely are a bad person who did wrong? Sigh. Itâ€™s sad to live in a world like this. If you donâ€™t like them or donâ€™t wanna like them anymore, itâ€™s up to you to just ignore. Donâ€™t flood them with these comments, youâ€™re hurting them too.

author: @user-xg4ht1zd7m
text:
I canâ€™t support this song because of the title, the lyrics, and the sets. We Japanese suffered an enormous earthquake in 2011, and over 10,000 people passed away. We canâ€™t forget such a huge earthquake, and Japanese members in NCT might think, too. (Some of the scenes in this track video remind me the 2011â€™s earthquake.) In addition, recently there are a lot of huge earthquakes in the southern Japan. We are living with the fears of happening earthquakes every day.
I know there are the culture differences, but this song will make people sad, and worried. I love NCT, and Iâ€™m such a huge fun of K-POP for a long time. I donâ€™t wanna see a lot of people will be sad by listening to NCTâ€™s song.
Please rethink about this song, and please think about the fans from overseas who have been suffered from earthquakes. 
Sorry about my bad English, but I just want you all to know about the fact.

author: @ririko2022
text:
Honesty, Earthquake is my trauma. East Japan eartquake gave our to too much damages. I can't accept this song and this concept... 'cause there are flames, collapsed buildings,and so on. These scenes digging up my memory of terrible eartquake.   NCT127 is boys group of active on a global stage. They,and their managers or producers should pay attention to natural disasters. Everyone should know that there are many people that hurt in heart because of disasters.

But,when they sang the word "tornado" we didn't point out it.  I have  feeling that we should don't accuse "Earthquake"of unscrupulous in defiance of that...    

Anyways, what I want to tell you in the end is, just, I was scared to see this Earthquake's directing. I don't want watch  that their cool performance to turn into fear through producing.

author: @angelmaymendoza8703
text:
Why you'd want to listen more than once: because it's a complex track.
On first my listen, Taeil, Yuta, and Doyoung's vocals are on point. Mark's parts, too - his voice and rap style suits the track so well. Best of all, Johnny's lines are THERE and are point. These stood out the most.
The track is all over the place (in the way that it has lots of layers) that I'd have to listen again - there were a lot of melodies and harmonizing behind the track and lead vocals probably that I wasn't able to appreciate every detail and every member on first listen.


And also, I was distracted by the visuals and the choreo. As per usual. HAHA here ends my first reaction review, now I'm off to listen to it again~

author: @myraclesname
text:
I'm so sorry to ruin the mood, but here's my criticism because it barely exists in this community. 
NCT has lost its flavor. 
I'm not saying that's a bad thing, but I'm not saying it's a good thing either. i enjoyed every subunits recent comeback but I've noticed how their distinctive sound has changed. Especially when it comes to 127. It hurts to say this, but they when will they release something exciting, something that we're used to yet not at all used to? I notice how I'm slowly falling out of being fan, maybe I've just lost my interest overall, but this song is a let down as well as the other subunit's track videos. Not music-wise, but nct and SM-wise. The styling is boring, the dances are so not nct (if that makes sense) and the sound is just... Generic. It's too "kpop" almost. I don't know how to explain it lol. But yeah I guess it's just my opinion. Accepting the fact that I might just not want to stan NCT anymore is harder than expected.

author: @rebeckaroy6790
text:
Yes siree, I had high expectations with a song title like Earthquake....  and 127 delivers :D  Really cool use of the drones... why are they being tracked?.....
I love how Mark uses his voice so playfully and later slides into some lovely vocals (and way to kill that choreo my son!)
TY is killing it in that sleeveless jumper and his approach to choreo and rap flow are soooo riveting
Love seeing Johnny getting the lines and centre these days, he feels like such an anchor to me
Yuta's vocal agility is getting even better, he cuts right through
Doyoung sounds divine as always and that is a good look for him, ,how is he always so elegant yet powerful?
Jungwoo makes the Hanson tshirt and cardigan look really work and his lines were soooo great
Haechan is just such a killer whenever he is on screen or in your ears, he knows how to make the most of every moment
Jaehyun was really bringing the drama in his scenes and I love to see those new angles
Yes, thank you, plenty of Taeil focus time in just this little track vid, keep it up editors!
